transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. I can help you today.

Speaker 2: Yeah, how you doing? My name is Roderick Hanson.

Speaker 1: I called and placed the order last Monday.

Speaker 2: Okay. I can take a look at that for you.

Speaker 1: Did you want to just track the order?

Speaker 2: No, no, no, no. I received the order Saturday.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: But the medicine vial was cracked.

Speaker 1: The bottle was cracked.

Speaker 2: And it was the only thing but six pills in it.

Speaker 1: I usually get the 18 pills.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah, let me take a look into that for you.

Speaker 1: What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 2: Hampton.

Speaker 1: And my zip code is 23223.

Speaker 2: Okay, and you said it came in damaged, correct?

Speaker 1: Yes, and I didn't want to take it because the bottle was cracked.

Speaker 2: The outside wrapping was sealed tight.

Speaker 1: It just said when I opened it up, it was cracked open,

Speaker 2: and it was nothing but six pills in it.

Speaker 1: Okay, let me just go ahead and notify the pharmacy.

Speaker 2: We're just going to send you a brand-new order.

Speaker 1: You'll get that in three to five business days.

Speaker 2: And aside from that, the one you have, just since it's damaged,

Speaker 1: just don't take it.

Speaker 2: Just dispose of it, but we'll send you one after.

Speaker 1: Yeah, that's what I was going to do.

Speaker 2: Okay. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no problem. I hope you have a good day.

Speaker 2: All right. Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.
